 23  /-- A chain is a subset `c` satisfying
 24    `x ≺ y ∨ x = y ∨ y ≺ x` for all `x y ∈ c`. -/
 25  def chain (c : set α) := pairwise_on c (λx y, x ≺ y ∨ y ≺ x)

 49  /-- `super_chain c₁ c₂` means that `c₂ is a chain that strictly includes `c₁`. -/
 50  def super_chain (c₁ c₂ : set α) : Prop := chain c₂ ∧ c₁ ⊂ c₂

 52  /-- A chain `c` is a maximal chain if there does not exists a chain strictly including `c`. -/
 53  def is_max_chain (c : set α) := chain c ∧ ¬ (∃c', super_chain c c')
